    <fact>
        <statement>
            <p>Suppose that <m>0&lt; p</m> and <m>p\neq 1</m>. Applying the integration power rule gives us the indefinite integral <m>\displaystyle \int \frac{1}{x^p} dx=\frac{1}{(1-p)}x^{1-p}+C</m>.</p>
        </statement>
    </fact>
